Ms. Nyx was born in my October 2020 litter. She was the feistiest of all 11 puppies. She went to a family in SD.
They reached out to me in January and said she had behavioral problems and they felt she was dangerous so they wanted to rehome her.

Per the contract they signed when buying her, they had to inform me first so I could decide what is best for the dog. I immediately brought her home. I didn't want a potentially dangerous dog being rehomed when I knew I could help her.

data.title: I am grateful to Imgur for taking it down. This is an apology for bad information, like I always do. I’m sorry.

images.description:
I have done the “correction post of shame” on numerous occasions, and I hate that I have to do it again on a post like this. However, I value integrity. I don’t like posting information that was later proven wrong without addressing that somehow. I have also been very distressed about Ukraine, and I feel terrible for this especially. 

.

I had already donated $20 to the Canadian Red Cross, but it didn’t feel like enough. I wanted to put in the last of my savings, but my stepmom said that was a terrible financial decision. She gave me that link instead, as a means of listing ways that someone could help that aren’t financial. 

.

It wasn’t malicious, she really did mean well. She said she got it from a regular law magazine website she reads (she’s a lawyer). 

.

I’m extremely grateful to Imgur for taking down bad information. As someone who does my best to post accurate and reliable information, I still felt that I owed y’all an apology. I was wrong, and I’m so sorry.

I thought that this was really cool! I was gifted this beautiful, massive piece of petrified wood today and asked if I would display it in Salamanderp Paradise. The couple who gifted it said that they found it in the 70s in Salt Lake City while digging up a plot of land to build the foundation of a new house. The petrified wood in that area is estimated to be about 225 MILLION years old! 

Petrified wood is created when wood is quickly covered by a layer of ash or sediment. It gets trapped and is unable to reach oxygen or elements that would help it break down. Still, slowly over hundreds of years it does break down little by little. As it does, voids are created in the wood. The voids are filled with surrounding minerals like silica, calcite, pyrite, and opal. This results in a fossil that has the texture and look of wood, but is instead made entirely of stone.

data.title: Ammo, Inc sending 1M Bullets to Ukraine

images.description:
SCOTTSDALE, Ariz. - A Scottsdale ammunition company is pledging to send one million bullets to Ukraine, after the nation's president made a plea for more supplies earlier this week.

AMMO, Inc., which is headquartered in Scottsdale, has pledge to send, free of charge, 1 million bullets to Ukraine. One of the bullets they make are called 762s - exactly what Ukrainian soldiers need to fight the Russia's invading army.

AMMO, Inc.'s CEO, Fred Wagenhals, is currently waiting for the government to approve the shipment, but already has his private plane ready to make the delivery, Fox 10 reported. It is not yet known if the government will approve.

https://www.fox10phoenix.com/news/russia-ukraine-war-scottsdale-ammo-company-to-send-1m-bullets-to-ukrainian-soldiers

Additionally, Remington, CCI, Speer and Federal Ammunition are collectively donating one-million rounds of ammo to the Ukraine Armed Forces.

https://www.ssusa.org/content/remington-cci-speer-federal-supporting-ukraine-with-one-million-round-ammunition-donation/

data.title: Two broken feet WITH THESE GAS PRICES

images.description:
I fractured my one foot and sprained the other. Hoping to be able to put pressure on one foot soon so I can at least get on crutches. 
My walk was going to be 2 miles there and I was excited to push myself to see what I can do. 
(Turns out I can’t properly walk down stairs) 

I’ve been laughing at the absurdity of it all.

I lost my sweet boy, Blue, today. I have no words to describe this feeling. We sent Blue to a training program to help with certain commands and responses. It was a three week program where he would be staying with the trainer in their home (some may have heard of the program, “Ty the Dog Guy.” He had been gone only a week and had made such great progress until this morning when the trainer called us saying she was at the urgent care with Blue because he was unresponsive. We raced over and the vet tells us that he suffered from a massive heatstroke. He came in with a temperature too high for the thermometer to register anything. A dog’s normal temp is 102. The thermometer’s max reading is 109. After pushing fluids, plasma, antibiotics, the works… he subsequently suffered from consecutive seizures. At which point, the vet had no hope and had even gotten a second opinion with a similar prognosis. He’s at rest now though. We went to see where he was staying at the trainers home to understand more. He was in a stifling travel carrier that he could barely fit in. He must’ve tried to get out and worked himself up so hot and in an anxiety. No one heard him or was able to help him. My wife feels so much blame. I feel so much regret. I’m so sad. I’m so angry. I feel so helpless. I don’t know what to do next. Thank you for listening.
